headline: Morgan Stanley Leans On AI And Tech IPOs As Valuation Stays Watchable
summary: Morgan Stanley rehired Michael Grimes as chairman of investment banking, signaling a renewed push into large technology IPOs that could include a future SpaceX listing. The firm is rolling out artificial intelligence tools in its wealth management arm to support advisor productivity and client service.
